## **BENCHMARKS THAT MATTER (FINANCIAL DIMENSION ONLY)**

### **AGI % Benchmarks:**

* **90-95%:** Pure labor services (consulting, design, strategy)  
* **85-90%:** Balanced mix (some media, mostly labor)  
* **75-85%:** Media-heavy or platform-fee models  
* **\<75%:** Very high pass-through (media buying, platform reseller)

### **Profit Margin Benchmarks:**

* **30%+:** Excellent (strong discipline, pricing power)  
* **20-30%:** Healthy (sustainable, reinvestment capacity)  
* **15-20%:** Acceptable (tight but viable)  
* **10-15%:** Concerning (limited runway, vulnerable)  
* **\<10%:** Critical (unsustainable without changes)

### **Revenue Scale Complexity Bands:**

* **\<$1.5M:** Solo/micro (founder-led, minimal infrastructure)  
* **$1.5M-$3M:** Small (emerging systems, early specialization)  
* **$3M-$10M:** Established small (formalized processes, management layer)  
* **$10M-$10M:** Mid-size (departmentalization, significant infrastructure)  
* **$10M+:** Large (full executive team, complex operations)

### **Cash Runway Benchmarks:**

* **6+ months:** Very healthy (strategic flexibility)  
* **3-6 months:** Healthy (standard cushion)  
* **1-3 months:** Tight (limited flexibility)  
* **\<1 month:** Critical (vulnerable)

